    dc:creator "Domínguez-Domínguez, Omar; Bernal-Zuñiga, Dulce María; Piller, Kyle R." ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Two new species of the genus Xenotoca Hubbs and Turner, 1939 (Teleostei, Goodeidae) from central-western Mexico" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263624>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.165689> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263624>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. a) Xenotoca doadrioi, Holotype male CPUM- 9589 and female from San Sebastian b) Xenotoca lyonsi, Holotype male CPUM- 9590 and female from Tamazula c) Xenotoca eiseni, male and female from Compostela population picture by Wolfgang Gessl www. pisces. at" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263624/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.165689>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distributional ranges of species in the Xenotoca eiseni group. Symbols correspond to specimens used in this study (black), localities of other known populations (dark gray), and historical localities that have not yielded specimens in the last 10 years or more (light gray). Stars correspond to Xenotoca eiseni from the Santiago River, circles for Xenotoca eiseni from the Compostela location, diamonds represent X. doadrioi, squares represents X. lyonsi, and triangles is for X. eiseni from Ameca and Armeria drainages never taxonomical or systematically analyzed. Numbers correspond to locations given in Table 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/165689/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

